  "prompt": "What distinguishes a good lawyer from a bad lawyer?",
  "response": "Here are some key qualities that distinguish a good lawyer from a bad one:\n\nGood lawyers typically:\n1. Have strong ethical standards\n2. Communicate clearly and regularly with clients\n3. Are thorough and detail-oriented\n4. Demonstrate extensive legal knowledge\n5. Prepare comprehensive case strategies\n6. Listen carefully to clients' needs\n7. Maintain professional integrity\n8. Manage time effectively\n9. Negotiate skillfully\n10. Stay updated on legal developments\n\nBad lawyers often:\n1. Lack transparency\n2. Fail to communicate consistently\n3. Show minimal effort or preparation\n4. Prioritize financial gain over client interests\n5. Miss important case details\n6. Provide inconsistent or unclear advice\n7. Lack professional boundaries\n8. Have poor time management skills\n9. Make unrealistic promises\n10. Demonstrate limited legal expertise\n\nThe most critical distinguishing factors are usually competence, ethics, and genuine commitment to serving clients' best interests.",
